Based on my investigation, here are the findings:

## Findings

### 1. Validation Logic Pattern in `LogConfig.java`

**`storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogConfig.java` lines 604-614:**
```java
private static void validateTopicLogConfigValues(Map<?, ?> props,
                                                 boolean isRemoteLogStorageSystemEnabled) {
    validateValues(props);
    boolean isRemoteLogStorageEnabled = (Boolean) props.get(TopicConfig.REMOTE_LOG_STORAGE_ENABLE_CONFIG);
    if (isRemoteLogStorageEnabled) {
        validateRemoteStorageOnlyIfSystemEnabled(props, isRemoteLogStorageSystemEnabled, false);
        validateNoRemoteStorageForCompactedTopic(props);
        validateRemoteStorageRetentionSize(props);
        validateRemoteStorageRetentionTime(props);
    }
}
```

**Finding:** All existing remote storage cross-validation methods are guarded by `if (isRemoteLogStorageEnabled)`. There is **NO cross-validation** added for `remote.log.disable.policy` - it is not checked whether this config should only be present when `remote.log.storage.enable=true`.

### 2. No Cross-Validation for `remote.log.disable.policy`

The PR adds the config to the `CONFIG` definition (lines 324-327 in the diff) with an `in()` validator:
```java
.define(TopicConfig.REMOTE_LOG_DISABLE_POLICY_CONFIG, STRING, TopicConfig.REMOTE_LOG_DISABLE_POLICY_RETAIN,
        in(TopicConfig.REMOTE_LOG_DISABLE_POLICY_RETAIN, TopicConfig.REMOTE_LOG_DISABLE_POLICY_DELETE),
        MEDIUM, TopicConfig.REMOTE_LOG_DISABLE_POLICY_DOC);
```

This only validates that the value is one of "retain" or "delete". It does **NOT** validate whether the config should be set at all when remote storage is disabled.

